      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Infantil ibuprofen is not suitable for an 8-year-old. I recommend using a child's ibuprofen product specifically designed for kids, and always follow the dosage instructions on the label. Typically, for an 8-year-old, a dose of 20-40 mg/kg every 6-8 hours, not to exceed 120 mg in 24 hours, is recommended. I recommend mixing it with a small amount of water or juice to make it easier for him to swallow.",
